"What’s your mental map of the emerging landscape of shared ownership in the U.S.?

He then made two videos about the map. The [https://www.loom.com/share/90d75a4fe7e54ff48af83f3706675f99 first] is a 3-minute overview with a bit of ecosystem history, and the [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YDmJmtlImiM&t=67s second] is an eloquent 13-minute personal commentary on the participants — i.e., the movement builders, the funders, the founders.

Felipe also talks about how we investors — yes, even us, we small-time members of a local food co-op, not just those fancy VC people — can participate in overcoming the violence and extraction in what he calls here our system of “capital supremacy.” And moving toward “livable future investing.”

(https://ownershipmatters.net/newsletter-item/issue-2-mapping-the-ecosystem/)

